1.title: Masked
1.plot: When Jaime Aguirre refuses to evict one of Altagracia's property for construction, she has him arrested; Saul, his son and lawyer gate-crashes one of Altagracia's parties.

2.title: Two Wills
2.plot: Saúl criticizes Altagracia for arresting his father, and she feigns indifference, but he managers to get to her.

3.title: Brutal Eviction
3.plot: Altagracia supervises the eviction of the neighborhood; One of the thugs attacks Mónica, and Saúl helps her; The neighborhood resists heroically.

4.title: Human Sacrifice
4.plot: Altagracia orders Guillermo's murder and sends a false confession to the press; Saúl accuses the Doña of not having a heart; Yesenia offers Lazaro an alliance.

5.title: Body As A Weapon
5.plot: Altagracia summons Saúl to arrive at an agreement and orders her employees out of the house; Lydia gives Mónica a makeover.

6.title: Disguised Desire
6.plot: Altagracia decides to withdraw her complaint against Jaime and shows up at the tenement to negotiate peace; Gabino gains Mónica's trust.

7.title: Tattoos And Clues
7.plot: Altagracia helps a wounded Margarita get to a hospital and later finds a connection between the tattoos of the men who attacked Margarita and those of the men who raped her and killed her parents.

8.title: Targeting the Killer
8.plot: Altagracia Sandoval has the information she needs, but first she must make sure Miguel Preciado is the Monkey she's after. Saul also travels to Veracruz.

9.title: Episode #1.9
9.plot: Altagracia employs her business persona to meet her worst enemy and causes an accident that forces him to reveal the tattoo that identifies him as the murderer.

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: Altagracia and Saul kiss for the first time. Ximena's suspicions that Saul is keeping things from her are confirmed after he admits he and Altagracia were together but didn't make love. Ximena breaks up with him and goes to Veracruz.

11.title: Episode #1.11
11.plot: Ximena surprises Lady Altagracia with a visit, but she's no match for Altagracia's shrewdness: a job offer in Madrid and a suitcase filled with money are enough to persuade her to leave the country. Saul rescues Monica.

12.title: Episode #1.12
12.plot: The fate of Miguel Preciado is in Altagracia's hands. Armed with a shotgun, she demands to know the names of his four accomplices. Meanwhile, Saul goes after Ximena at the airport.

13.title: Episode #1.13
13.plot: Braulio is charged with torturing Miguel Preciado for information, Monica has high hopes for her and Saul, and Felipe discovers that Lady Altagracia has been drugging him to sexually incapacitate him.

14.title: Episode #1.14
14.plot: Felipe discovers that Altagracia used him to acquire more properties and decides to get revenge on her for humiliating him. Gabino steals a kiss from Monica, who tells him she's in love with someone else.

15.title: Episode #1.15
15.plot: News of the expropriation infuriate Saul, who finds Altagracia and tells her that her strategy of seducing him so he'd let his guard down worked. They kiss and Felipe catches them red-handed.

16.title: Episode #1.16
16.plot: Saul wakes up from the coma and swears to get revenge on Felipe, but Altagracia talks him out of it. Meanwhile, Miguel Preciado recognizes one of his accomplices, a colonel, and Valeria seduces Lopecito.

17.title: Episode #1.17
17.plot: Monica visits Saul at the hospital and questions him. He tries to find out if she knows anything and tells her he loves her like a little sister. Lady Altagracia gets revenge on Miguel Preciado.

18.title: Episode #1.18
18.plot: Saul is discharged from the hospital and he and Altagracia make love for the first time. Meanwhile, Lady Altagracia and Felipe's divorce is made official and Valeria belittles Lopecito.

19.title: Episode #1.19
19.plot: At a press conference, Felipe confirms that he and Lady Altagracia are no longer together and accuses her of swindling him. Monica suspects Saul and Altagracia spent the night together and becomes distant.

20.title: Episode #1.20
20.plot: Lady Altagracia tells Saul and her team that she won't fight for the Aguirres' tenement, Yesenia tries to give Saul a reality check, and it's decided that Braulio will run for Congress.

21.title: Episode #1.21
21.plot: Saul is the main suspect in Miguel Preciado's disappearance and he lets Lady Altagracia know he's upset about it. Monica remains oblivious to the fact that Lazaro's not her real father.

22.title: Episode #1.22
22.plot: Felipe wakes up with a gun in his hand and an unpleasant surprise, Lazaro shows symptoms of another illness, and Monica gives Saul a rude awakening after he finds her and Gabino together.

23.title: Episode #1.23
23.plot: Saul, trying to find out the truth about what happened to Miguel Preciado, goes with Lopecito to Veracruz, where they trace Preciado's last steps. Meanwhile, Lady Altagracia visits Felipe in prison and gives Monica money.

24.title: Episode #1.24
24.plot: Yesenia visits Lady Altagracia to tell her that her daughter died, but Altagracia refuses to believe it. Regina tries to get Altagracia to open up, but fails. Altagracia blames Lazaro for her daughter's death and Felipe recants on TV.

25.title: Episode #1.25
25.plot: Yesenia goads Lazaro into making Altagracia pay for the time and money she cheated him out of and Monica wants to know the truth about her father's health.

26.title: Episode #1.26
26.plot: Altagracia tells Saul her deepest secret as proof of her love for him, Lazaro tells Felipe what Altagracia did to him, and the congressman decides to help him get revenge.

27.title: Episode #1.27
27.plot: Altagracia is almost kidnapped on the street, but Monica intervenes. Later, she learns that Monica was abandoned by her mother after she was born and is reminded by Braulio of her revenge.

28.title: Episode #1.28
28.plot: Altagracia is relentless with Saul, Felipe confirms that Monica is Altagracia's daughter, and Yesenia foresees something horrible in Monica's future after a Tarot card reading.

29.title: Episode #1.29
29.plot: Cespedes is a high-ranking military officer feared by his subordinates. Years ago he shot Cesar, Lady Altagracia's boyfriend, but now, he and Altagracia meet once again to close a deal.

30.title: Episode #1.30
30.plot: A visit from his old friend Alejandro Cespedes puts Rafael on edge, Altagracia gets upset when Monica doesn't show up at the company to work, and Monica kisses Gabino, but later turns him down.

31.title: Episode #1.31
31.plot: Emiliano runs over Lydia and flees the scene with Isabela, but Saul manages to see the license plate and posts it online. Altagracia offers Monica a job as an assistant, and Emiliano, racked with guilt, OD's.

32.title: Episode #1.32
32.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

33.title: Episode #1.33
33.plot: Saul forces Altagracia to choose a side, Rafael pays off Gabino, and Yesenia kisses Lazaro, who's suspicious of her intentions at first but is then put at ease by a skillful Yesenia.

34.title: Episode #1.34
34.plot: Colonel Cespedes is arrested after Lady Altagracia has drugs planted on the truck carrying his wood, Yesenia and Lazaro make up, and Felipe employs a journalist to uncover one of Lady Altagracia's secrets.

35.title: Episode #1.35
35.plot: Saul blindly defends Altagracia from his father's accusations. Braulio becomes Colonel Cespedes' defense attorney and asks him not to say anything about Altagracia. Yesenia and Lazaro cannot cash the check.

36.title: Episode #1.36
36.plot: Jaime visits Altagracia and demands she leave Saul alone, Leticia's hypocrisy drives Emiliano to record a video of himself using drugs, which Saul sees, and Yesenia reveals her identity to Monica and Isabela.

37.title: Episode #1.37
37.plot: Saul tells Ximena that he loves Altagracia. She accuses her of being manipulative and admits Lady Altagracia paid her to leave the country. Rafael starts looking for Daniel Llamas.

38.title: Episode #1.38
38.plot: Gabino brutally beats up Adolfo after seeing him consoling Monica. Ximena confronts Altagracia and warns Monica about her intentions. The journalist finds a clue.

39.title: Episode #1.39
39.plot: Altagracia sees Saul looking at pictures of Ximena and gets jealous, but they end up making love. Afterwards, she tells him about Ximena's abortion and Saul confronts his ex.

40.title: Episode #1.40
40.plot: Saul tries his best to prove Emiliano's guilty, but still loses the case and Matamoros plans Cespedes' release so he can get rid of him.

41.title: Episode #1.41
41.plot: Altagracia and Ximena argue at the tenement, the residents gang up on Lady Altagracia, but Saul demands they respect her. Meanwhile, Colonel Cespedes finds himself face to face with Altagracia, who recognizes him as a Monkey.

42.title: Episode #1.42
42.plot: Altagracia reveals herself to Cespedes and tortures him until he confesses his crimes, Monica is kicked out of the construction company, and Regina can't make love to Felipe.

43.title: Episode #1.43
43.plot: Ximena lies to Jaime about Lady Altagracia's intentions, which enrages him and drives him to go to the construction site to face her. Instead, he is met by Braulio, with whom he struggles until he falls to his death while Saul watches.

44.title: Episode #1.44
44.plot: A shocked Saul refuses to believe in Altagracia's innocence. Braulio keeps her from being arrested, Yesenia refuses to testify on her behalf, and Monica consoles Saul.

45.title: Episode #1.45
45.plot: Yesenia lies to Saul with Lazaro's help, Altagracia performs a ritual to compel Yesenia into telling the truth, and Margarita tells Saul that Lady Altagracia threatened her.

46.title: Episode #1.46
46.plot: Saul relentlessly questions everything Altagracia has told him, but she insists that she's innocent. Yesenia refuses to help her, which drives Lady Altagracia to threaten her with a gun.

47.title: Episode #1.47
47.plot: Braulio has dream in which Altagracia reproaches him for killing Jaime during a sexual encounter. Meanwhile, Altagracia asks Monica to intercede on her behalf and Monica helps Saul look for the killer.

48.title: Episode #1.48
48.plot: Saul confronts Braulio and both threaten to kill each other. Altagracia chides Monica for her lack of loyalty and decides have her investigated.

49.title: Episode #1.49
49.plot: Gabino's obsession with Monica becomes unbearable, Altagracia and Regina fight over Monica, Cespedes forces Matamoros to drive him to Lady Altagracia's house, and Valeria finds out she's pregnant with Lopecito's child.

50.title: Episode #1.50
50.plot: Altagracia, already expecting Cespedes' visit, kills him, but upon carrying out her revenge feels empty. Gabino assaults Monica, who recognizes him though he's wearing a mask.

51.title: Episode #1.51
51.plot: Altagracia finds out about Regina and Felipe and reacts ruthlessly. Rafael entrusts Gabino with getting Karen out of the city, and Saul struggles to suspect Daniel.

52.title: Episode #1.52
52.plot: Altagracia kicks Regina out of the house, who goes to a hotel with Isabela. Braulio finds out Lazaro is Monica's father, and Karen holds her ground with Gabino. Meanwhile, Lady Altagracia's heart turns cold.

53.title: Episode #1.53
53.plot: After he finds out the truth about Monica, Braulio threatens to kill Yesenia and Lazaro. Altagracia devises a way to see Daniel's tattoo and Saul decides he's willing to murder for justice.

54.title: Episode #1.54
54.plot: Saul dumps Altagracia and declares war on her. Rafael discovers Altagracia was one of his victims and Altagracia tells Azucena Ximena's secret.

55.title: Episode #1.55
55.plot: Yesenia and Lazaro make love. During a fight with Monica over Saul, Altagracia threatens Monica's father. Monica leaves her job at the foundation.

56.title: Episode #1.56
56.plot: Altagracia finds Lazaro and tells him the truth about their daughter to get even with Yesenia. Later, she decides to show Monica how powerful she is and sends Gabino after her, but Saul beats him up.

57.title: Episode #1.57
57.plot: Saul kisses Monica in an attempt to stop her from moving away. Altagracia orders Gabino not to hurt Saul and performs a ritual to make Regina and Isabela return. Meanwhile, Lazaro's condition worsens.

58.title: Episode #1.58
58.plot: Monica and Margarita are unfairly arrested for contraband and jailed. Altagracia spoils Isabela as if she were her daughter. An enraged Yesenia goes after Altagracia and threatens her with a knife.

59.title: Episode #1.59
59.plot: Saul breaks into Altagracia's room with a gun and confronts her about Monica's disappearance. She tries to kiss him, but he turns her away. Gabino offers Monica the chance to run away with him.

60.title: Episode #1.60
60.plot: Monica manages to get in touch with Saul, who comes to her aid. He's given 144 hours to build up his defense. The forensic scientist betrays Braulio and admits he got rid of evidence.

61.title: Episode #1.61
61.plot: Monica confronts the prison bully to save the life of a fellow inmate, but is sent along with Margarita to isolation as punishment for it. Meanwhile, Lopecito stops Valeria from getting an abortion.

62.title: Episode #1.62
62.plot: Altagracia finds out Braulio killed Jaime, but can't betray him because he knows all her secrets. Monica puts up with the abuse in prison and sings to give herself and others hope.

63.title: Episode #1.63
63.plot: Gabino informs Rafael that the oldest daughter of the Sandovals survived and went to the police to unsuccessfully report her attackers. Saul bribes the prison warden so she'll move Monica out of isolation.

64.title: Episode #1.64
64.plot: Braulio confesses and Altagracia goes to see Saul with the evidence, but he refuses to believe in her innocence. Monica calls Lazaro and comforts him. Meanwhile, Saul asks Valeria to be his ally.

65.title: Episode #1.65
65.plot: Saul, enraged and filled with hatred, goes after Braulio to kill him despite Azucena and Valeria's pleas. Altagracia pays Monica a visit after hours to intimidate her.

66.title: Episode #1.66
66.plot: Saul pays Monica a "conjugal" visit. He promises to get her out and advises her about the trial. Altagracia threatens Gabino and demands he provide solid proof that'll incriminate Monica.

67.title: Episode #1.67
67.plot: Braulio finds the cameras Ximena planted in his room and gets rid of her. Saul's defense is convincing, but Altagracia pressures Valeria into finding Monica guilty.

68.title: Episode #1.68
68.plot: Valeria finds Monica and Margarita not guilty. Braulio gets rid of Ximena's body. Altagracia follows Monica to the hospital and finds Lazaro.

69.title: Episode #1.69
69.plot: Monica and Saul make love. Altagracia stops Gabino from attacking Monica. Regina tries to get Altagracia to back down, but she refuses to give up Saul and accept Monica as her daughter.

70.title: Episode #1.70
70.plot: Altagracia orders Yesenia to come between Monica and Saul by encouraging Monica's relationship with Adolfo. Yesenia confirms Altagracia's alibi. Leticia decides to investigate Rafael.

71.title: Episode #1.71
71.plot: Yesenia mistakenly tells Saul that Altagracia was a victim of The Monkeys. Altagracia wants to find Francisco, the fourth Monkey. Saul tells the police about Braulio.

72.title: Episode #1.72
72.plot: Monica goes to see Altagracia to turn down the money she gave her for Lazaro's treatment. Lady Altagracia brags about Saul's love for her. Karen arrests Braulio, who defends himself skillfully.

73.title: Episode #1.73
73.plot: Saul tries to apologize to Altagracia, but she'll only forgive him if he meets her at the ranch, an offer Saul finds hard to resist.

74.title: Episode #1.74
74.plot: Saul sees Monica as an embodiment of calmness and tranquility, while Altagracia's a storm who unsettles him. Monica demands Saul he stay away from Altagracia and Leticia releases Felipe's video montage.

75.title: Episode #1.75
75.plot: Francisco Vega threatens to rape Isabela if Altagracia doesn't tell him who else knows about him. Meanwhile, Rafael admits to Leticia that he was a Monkey, but that he changed for love.

76.title: Episode #1.76
76.plot: Francisco seeks Rafael and Daniel's help. He plans to make Altagracia talk so they can kill her. Rafael is beaten is taken to Altagracia.

77.title: Episode #1.77
77.plot: Altagracia tells Rafael about her revenge against the Monkeys and tell him only Matamoros knows. Daniel tries to talk Francisco out of killing Altagracia, but is threatened instead. Meanwhile, Lazaro's health deteriorates.

78.title: Episode #1.78
78.plot: Leticia takes an entire bottle of pills out of desperation, Altagracia tells Rafael that she had a daughter with one of the Monkeys, a piece of information that he shares with Daniel.

79.title: Episode #1.79
79.plot: Francisco threatens Rafael so Altagracia will talk, a thug tries to rape Altagracia, but Daniel stops him and is shot. Later, he manages to alert Saul.

80.title: Episode #1.80
80.plot: Rafael shoots Francisco to save Altagracia, who finishes her kidnapper off after telling him that she'll go after his family next. Rafael keeps the motives of the kidnapping a secret from Saul.

81.title: Episode #1.81
81.plot: Altagracia sends Saul away when she learns he's with Monica, Isabela dumps Emiliano, who gets drugged and has a motorcycle accident. Monica agrees to meet with Saul to say goodbye.

82.title: Episode #1.82
82.plot: Rafael blames Monica for Emiliano's death and swears he'll kill her to avenge his son. Monica takes a blood test to help Lazaro. Yesenia tells Altagracia that Monica is leaving Saul.

83.title: Episode #1.83
83.plot: Monica finds out she's not Lazaro's biological daughter after she takes the blood test. Saul goes to Monica to profess his love for her. Lazaro tells Altagracia that Monica doesn't need her in her life.

84.title: Episode #1.84
84.plot: Daniel admits to Altagracia that she was the love of his life, but she tortures him so he'll reveal the identity of the fifth Monkey. Saul goes through Braulio's car and finds one of Ximena's earrings.

85.title: Episode #1.85
85.plot: Altagracia tries to seduce Daniel to get him to talk. Braulio drugs Lydia, rapes her, and calls Diego. Monica and Adolfo find out that Lazaro signed his company away to Altagracia.

86.title: Episode #1.86
86.plot: Monica visits Regina to find out whether Altagracia's her mother. Diego punches Braulio. Lydia wakes up and accuses Braulio of drugging her. Altagracia and Saul kiss.

87.title: Episode #1.87
87.plot: Gabino kidnaps Monica and Adolfo and takes them to a desolate place so he can carry out his plan of faking a crime of passion. Monica tells Gabino she's Altagracia's daughter so he won't kill her.

88.title: Episode #1.88
88.plot: Gabino beats up Monica and tells her she was conceived during a rape before throwing her off a cliff. Altagracia rescues her and has Gabino tortured. Meanwhile, Saul attacks Braulio and is arrested for it.

89.title: Episode #1.89
89.plot: Altagracia makes Gabino pay for everything he did to Monica. Monica has surgery so she won't lose her arm. Altagracia prays for her safety in her private altar. Saul is desperate in prison.

90.title: Episode #1.90
90.plot: Altagracia tells Monica her father was an old boyfriend of hers and that she abandoned her to become Lady Altagracia. Monica swears she will avenge Lazaro. Karen finds parts of Braulio's car.

91.title: Episode #1.91
91.plot: Altagracia asks Daniel to tell her who the fifth Monkey is, offers him a life together, and tells him she wishes he were Monica's father. Monica tells Saul the truth.

92.title: Episode #1.92
92.plot: Braulio, feeling betrayed by Altagracia's disdain, finds out about Valeria's affair with Lopecito and threatens to kill Leticia to draw out his enemy and get revenge. Meanwhile, Daniel refuses to run away.

93.title: Episode #1.93
93.plot: Daniel returns to the foundation and tells Monica that he could be her father. Felipe has Saul released from jail while Braulio's sent to prison. Altagracia asks Saul to leave both her and Monica.

94.title: Episode #1.94
94.plot: Daniel is willing to turn himself over to the police, but Altagracia doesn't allow it for fear of being exposed. Monica rejects Daniel feeling disgust for him. Leticia protects Rafael.

95.title: Episode #1.95
95.plot: Rafael finds Monica's DNA profile and decides to find out whether she's his daughter. He dreams of earning her forgiveness and raising her with Leticia. Meanwhile, Altagracia asks him if he knows Daniel Llamas.

96.title: Episode #1.96
96.plot: Lazaro and Yesenia get married at the tenement in a touching ceremony. Daniel manages to get away from Matamoros and meets Rafael so they can go get the DNA test.

97.title: Episode #1.97
97.plot: Altagracia changes her look and becomes Lady Altagracia once again to attend an event where she seduces a Norwegian investor to forget Saul.

98.title: Episode #1.98
98.plot: Monica stops Altagracia from killing Rafael. Cornered, Braulio threatens to reveal Altagracia's crimes if she doesn't help him walk out of his trial unscathed. Lazaro collapses.

99.title: Episode #1.99
99.plot: Felipe shows up at the construction company as the new Secretary of Urban Development and tells Altagracia that her company's days are numbered, for he plans to destroy her and her empire.

100.title: Episode #1.100
100.plot: Altagracia apologizes to Lazaro for everything she did to him and tells him a white lie so he'll die in peace. Meanwhile, Monica demands both Rafael and Daniel turn themselves over to the police.

101.title: Episode #1.101
101.plot: Saul and Monica reunite in front of Lazaro's grave while Altagracia watches them from afar. Felipe hinders Lady Altagracia's latest project and her investors demand she get him out of the way.

102.title: Episode #1.102
102.plot: Braulio bribes the prison guards who help him escape by hiding him among the dirty laundry. Altagracia has Rafael kill Felipe to prevent him from accusing them of their crimes.

103.title: Episode #1.103
103.plot: Daniel asks Monica to replace him at the foundation and tells the women about his dark past. Karen searches for proof in the ranch's basement. Rafael has Felipe in his sights.

104.title: Episode #1.104
104.plot: After proposing to Regina, Felipe is killed along with Gustavo. Matamoros records Rafael during the murder. Karen confronts Altagracia with the evidence gathered at the ranch's basement.

105.title: Episode #1.105
105.plot: Braulio stabs the forensic scientist and strangles the hotel waiter who testified against him. Altagracia sends Karen the video of Felipe's murder to incriminate Rafael.

106.title: Episode #1.106
106.plot: Braulio kidnaps Yesenia to lure in Monica and calls Altagracia so she'll hear him kill her daughter. Yesenia does one last act of love for her adoptive daughter Monica.

107.title: Episode #1.107
107.plot: Monica blames her mother for all the pain and suffering in her life. Altagracia, feeling abandoned, decides to try to win back Saul and Adolfo proposes to Monica. Meanwhile, Braulio and Rafael join forces against Lady Altagracia.

108.title: Episode #1.108
108.plot: Monica declines Adolfo's proposal. Filled with resentment, Adolfo confronts Saul and blames him for coming between Monica and Altagracia.

109.title: Episode #1.109
109.plot: Altagracia arrives at Daniel's tenement just in time to stop him from committing suicide. She decides to hide him in her house and tap his phone to get to Rafael. Meanwhile, Diego recues Lydia.

110.title: Episode #1.110
110.plot: Altagracia tells Saul that she's changed, that she saved Daniel and wants to help him. Karen and Jorge find Elena's body. Adolfo and Monica reconcile. Lady Altagracia is content.

111.title: Episode #1.111
111.plot: Altagracia uses Daniel to make Saul jealous and succeeds in her endeavor. Braulio apologizes to Diego and admits he's insane. Monica tries to force herself to forget Saul and love Adolfo.

112.title: Episode #1.112
112.plot: Braulio sets up an explosion and Saul and Altagracia live through dangerous moments that bring them closer together. Monica can't stop thinking about Saul despite Adolfo's efforts to woo her. Regina makes a discovery.

113.title: Episode #1.113
113.plot: Altagracia takes Saul to her secret room and summons her personal witch doctor, Lucio, to heal him and to perform a love ritual so Saul takes her back. Monica breaks up with Adolfo.

114.title: Episode #1.114
114.plot: Braulio sets off the earthquake alarm so Rafael can get to Altagracia while she's unprotected. Monica decides to help a battered woman, but is faced by thugs.

115.title: Episode #1.115
115.plot: Rafael manages to force Altagracia to confess her crimes and tries to rape her, but she slits his throat. Meanwhile, Lucio reinitiates the love ritual on Saul and Altagracia gets naked to wake him up.

116.title: Episode #1.116
116.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

117.title: Episode #1.117
117.plot: Saul rescues the sex slaves during a dangerous mission. Leticia records everything but cannot report the story because she's fired. Karen also loses her job and Monica kisses Saul.

118.title: Episode #1.118
118.plot: Monica and Saul lead a women's rights protest. Altagracia and Braulio meet again. He goes after Valeria and has an unexpected end. Diego gets the video.

119.title: Episode #1.119
119.plot: Saul proposes to Monica. Diego decides to post the video online and everyone condemns Altagracia. Monica gets ready for her wedding with Saul in Veracruz. Altagracia shows up armed.

120.title: Episode #1.120
120.plot: Altagracia struggles with her anger towards Saul but ends up allowing him to be happy with Monica. Though mother and daughter forgive each other, Lady Altagracia faces a manhunt.

imdb.plot outline: "La Doña," based on the literary work of Rómulo Gallegos "Doña Bárbara," is a story of revenge and ambition, seduction and betrayal. Told from the perspective of an abused woman named Altagracia, she represents the hundreds of thousands of Mexican women who have been victims of violence by men who are protected by impunity and a patriarchal culture. In Altagracia's case, these men are five teenagers from prominent families who rape her as a child and murder her parents. Having picked herself and her sister up from the ashes, Altagracia became a ruthless, strong-willed devourer of men, and with the fortune of an ex-husband, "La Doña" looks to bring her abusers, and any others she finds along the way, to her own brand of justice.
imdb.title: Lady Altagracia
plot: Worlds collide and lives shatter when Altagracia, a powerful and elegant businesswoman, plots a twisted revenge while falling in love.

"La Doña," based on the literary work of Rómulo Gallegos "Doña Bárbara," is a story of revenge and ambition, seduction and betrayal. Told from the perspective of an abused woman named Altagracia, she represents the hundreds of thousands of Mexican women who have been victims of violence by men who are protected by impunity and a patriarchal culture. In Altagracia's case, these men are five teenagers from prominent families who rape her as a child and murder her parents. Having picked herself and her sister up from the ashes, Altagracia became a ruthless, strong-willed devourer of men, and with the fortune of an ex-husband, "La Doña" looks to bring her abusers, and any others she finds along the way, to her own brand of justice.
